 The user spends most of their meaningful cognitive effort in **Planning** and **Beads**. The later stages are mostly machine-tending, review, intervention, and quality convergence. The engineering roadmap mirrors that distribution: cockpit + setup first, then plan creation and bead curation, before pouring months into perfect swarm telemetry.
 
+
+### 0.1 Hybridization decisions added in this revision
+
+This revision keeps the original architecture's load-bearing choices — the VPS daemon, SSH tunnel by default, origin/VPS/local-clone source-of-truth split, Go daemon, t3code desktop lift, and skill-attached tending jobs — but tightens the execution plan in places where a production team would otherwise lose time later.
+
+The major additions are:
+
+- a concrete transport ladder and desktop `ConnectionManager` finite-state machine;
+- a seed REST/WS/API contract so the daemon is buildable before the full OpenAPI file exists;
+- a daemon process-management contract covering semaphores, cancellation, ring buffers, log persistence, and backpressure;
+- an explicit desktop local-data layer for read-only FTS/search and warm startup, without violating the canonical-source rule;
+- structured ACFS/bootstrap phase parsing with raw-log fallback;
+- plan artifact layout, plan-cost ledger, content-addressed LLM cache, and cost caps;
+- bead curation, polish scoring, graph-performance thresholds, and convergence metrics;
+- worktree-isolated health scans so coverage/complexity jobs do not trample swarm edits;
+- direct-vs-delegated review execution modes;
+- milestone acceptance tests and production smoke checks.
+
+The result should be less hand-wavy at the implementation layer while still preserving the original plan's most important strategic constraint: Hoopoe is a cockpit around the Flywheel, not a replacement engine.
+
