+### 1.9 Vertical slices beat feature silos
+
+Every milestone must ship at least one end-to-end path through the real remote stack. A beautiful Planning screen that cannot write artifacts to the VPS is less valuable than a plain editor that can generate, persist, lock, and convert a plan. A polished graph animation is less valuable than a basic Kanban that round-trips through `br` and survives reconnect.
+
+The walking skeleton therefore starts with: connect to VPS → install daemon → stream one remote job → import one project → read one `br` list → convert one plan → launch one tiny swarm. The UI can be ugly in the earliest cuts; the data path cannot be fake.
+
+### 1.10 Measurable fitness functions for each stage
+
+A stage is not "done" because the UI exists. It is done when its real-world fitness functions pass:
+
+| Area | Fitness function |
+| --- | --- |
+| Onboarding | A fresh supported VPS reaches `vps_ready` without opening a terminal outside Hoopoe; failures resume from the last checkpoint. |
+| Planning | A one-paragraph idea produces persisted candidate plans, comparison, synthesis, refinement, a locked `plan.md`, and a cost/audit ledger. |
+| Beads | A locked plan converts into real `br` beads; traceability covers plan sections; the DAG has no cycles unless explicitly accepted. |
+| Swarm | A small mixed swarm launches, registers with Agent Mail, claims beads, reserves files, commits, pushes, and streams state back after laptop sleep. |
+| Hardening | Health snapshots run in isolated worktrees; review findings resolve into fixes/beads/false positives; convergence is visible. |
+| Recovery | Killing the desktop, daemon, or tunnel never loses canonical work; reconnect reconstructs the UI from audit/events/canonical tools. |
+
+These fitness functions are carried into §18 as concrete acceptance tests.
