+### 3.1 Desktop local data layer
+
+The desktop keeps two kinds of local state and must not blur them.
+
+**Authoritative local-only state:** window layout, stage route, command palette MRU, user settings, keybindings, cached bearer/session metadata, connection profiles, update channel, and UI preferences.
+
+**Read-through remote cache:** project summaries, plan metadata, bead summaries, graph edges, mail/activity snippets, health summaries, recent audit events, and search indexes. These rows carry `sourceSequence`, `sourceSha`, `snapshotTime`, or `etag` so the renderer can show stale state honestly. They can be deleted and rebuilt from the daemon plus canonical tools.
+
+Suggested SQLite tables for the desktop cache:
+
+```text
+vps_profiles(id, host, user, port, last_seen, status)
+projects(id, name, origin_url, active_branch, source_sequence, last_opened)
+plans(id, project_id, title, state, locked_sha, updated_at, source_sequence)
+plan_fts(plan_id, title, body)                       # FTS5 if SQLite
+bead_meta(project_id, bead_id, title, status, priority, type, labels, source_sequence)
+bead_fts(bead_id, title, body, labels)                # FTS5 if SQLite
+bead_deps(project_id, from_bead_id, to_bead_id, source_sequence)
+activity_events(project_id, sequence, category, summary, unread, created_at)
+mail_messages(project_id, message_id, thread_id, sender, subject, snippet, created_at)
+health_summaries(project_id, commit_sha, coverage, avg_complexity, hotspots, created_at)
+clone_state(project_id, path, last_fetched_sha, dirty_local, size_bytes, updated_at)
+```
+
+No canonical mutation is considered complete because the desktop cache says so. Mutations go through daemon RPCs; the desktop may show a local pending badge but must reconcile against daemon acks and canonical state before removing the badge.
+
